ts pay for outcomes, not hours. AI leverage should be used to increase capacity or deliver deeper work, not to lower prices. Consultants who discount because AI made them faster commodity themselves. The right move is to keep rates and reinvest the time savings into better deliverables or more clients."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which AI tools should a solo consultant avoid buying?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Solo consultants should skip enterprise sales tools like Apollo, Clay, or Outreach, which are built for sales teams running high volumes. Marketing automation platforms like Marketo or HubSpot Marketing Hub are also overkill. Large agency-style AI suites are not cost-effective when you are running two to five client engagements at a time."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What AI tool helps consultants with meeting notes and follow-ups?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Fathom is the top AI meeting note tool for solo consultants. It records, transcribes, and summarizes calls automatically, then routes summaries into your CRM. The free tier handles most solo consultant needs. The $30/month Pro tier adds unlimited storage and custom summary templates."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is there a free AI tool for solo consultants just getting started?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The free tier of Claude.ai, the free version of Fathom for meeting notes, HubSpot CRM free, and Linear free for project tracking give you a functional starting stack at zero cost. For serious client work, upgrading Claude to $20/month and adding Perplexity Pro at $20/month delivers the biggest productivity gains."}}]}</script>
